05/11/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Over 500,000 civil servants staged a 24-hour general strike on Tuesday (4 November), along with teachers, university professors, doctors and port employees. <I>Kathimerini</I> reported that state hospitals are functioning on skeleton staff, and Olympic Airways has cancelled 19 domestic flights. Government spokesman Christos Protopapas said if the government yields to demands for a 20 per cent wage increase, the country would have to resort to new foreign financing. (Kathimerini - 05/11/03; MPA - 04/11/03)
